ManagedElementType.name: ManagedElementType
ManagedElementType.description: Type of a managed base hardware element (slot, port, power supply, fan, etc.) on a device.

ConfigRedundancy.name: ConfigRedundancy
ConfigRedundancy.description: An indication of whether a hardware slot is empty, stand-alone, or part of a redundant pair.

HardwareState.name: HardwareState
HardwareState.description: The high-level hardware state (active, initializing, standby, etc.).

HardwareStateQual.name: HardwareStateQual
HardwareStateQual.description: Further qualification/detail on the high-level hardware state.

ExtendedSlot.name: ExtendedSlot
ExtendedSlot.description: An identifier of either a slot or a hardware component. Slot numbers, slot11 to slot14 are valid on NX device, and refer to slot1 to slot4 on that device.

LineType.name: LineType
LineType.description: An indication of whether a port is copper or optical.

DuplexState.name: DuplexState
DuplexState.description: An indication of whether a port is running in full or half duplex mode.

SfpQualifier.name: SfpQualifier
SfpQualifier.description: SFP qualifier value. These combines both the compliance codes for the 1G SFP and 10G SFP+, and transmitter technology for the 40G QSFP+ and 10G XFP transceivers.

hw_slotTable.name: hw_slotTable
hw_slotTable.description: Table of slots/ports on the device.

hw_slotEntry.name: hw_slotEntry
hw_slotEntry.description: An entry in the slot/port table. Rows cannot be created or deleted.

slotNumber.name: slotNumber
slotNumber.description: Slot number for this hardware element.

slotPort.name: slotPort
slotPort.description: Port number for this hardware element (0 refers to the board).

slotType.name: slotType
slotType.description: Type of hardware element corresponding to slot/port.

slotCfgType.name: slotCfgType
slotCfgType.description: The configuration/redundancy of a hardware element.

slotRunState.name: slotRunState
slotRunState.description: The high-level hardware state (active, initializing, standby, etc.).

slotQualifier1.name: slotQualifier1
slotQualifier1.description: Further qualification/detail on the high-level hardware state.

slotQualifier2.name: slotQualifier2
slotQualifier2.description: Further qualification/detail on the high-level hardware state.

slotQualifier3.name: slotQualifier3
slotQualifier3.description: Further qualification/detail on the high-level hardware state.

slotQualifier4.name: slotQualifier4
slotQualifier4.description: Further qualification/detail on the high-level hardware state.

slotStartTime.name: slotStartTime
slotStartTime.description: The time (seconds) at which this hardware element was powered up.

slotVendorID.name: slotVendorID
slotVendorID.description: The identifying number of the vendor of this hardware.

slotDeviceID.name: slotDeviceID
slotDeviceID.description: The PCI bus device ID for this slot.

slotProductID.name: slotProductID
slotProductID.description: Versioning and other inventory information for this hardware element.

slotFPGAVersion.name: slotFPGAVersion
slotFPGAVersion.description: The version of the TPT FPGA chip on this hardware.

slotInterface.name: slotInterface
slotInterface.description: The entry in the IF-MIB interface table that corresponds to this port.

slotLineType.name: slotLineType
slotLineType.description: The line type (e.g., copper or optical) of the port.

slotDuplexState.name: slotDuplexState
slotDuplexState.description: The current duplex state (full or half) of the port.

slotPhysical.name: slotPhysical
slotPhysical.description: Physical port number for this hardware element (0 if not a port).

slotSfpQualifier2.name: slotSfpQualifier2
slotSfpQualifier2.description: Type of the SFP transceiver. This is applicable to the dual speed transceivers, and this variable will have value of the second speed supported by those transceivers. For single-speed transceivers, the value will be not applicable.

hw_chasTable.name: hw_chasTable
hw_chasTable.description: Table of chassis data for the device. Represented as a table with one row, and that row is the same as that for other managed elements.

hw_chasEntry.name: hw_chasEntry
hw_chasEntry.description: An entry in the chassis table. Rows cannot be created or deleted.

chasNumber.name: chasNumber
chasNumber.description: Number for this entry in the chassis table. Should always be 0.

chasType.name: chasType
chasType.description: Type of hardware element -- should always be chassis or unequip.

chasCfgType.name: chasCfgType
chasCfgType.description: The configuration/redundancy of a hardware element.

chasRunState.name: chasRunState
chasRunState.description: The high-level hardware state (active, initializing, standby, etc.).

chasDeviceID.name: chasDeviceID

tptHardwareNotifyDeviceID.name: tptHardwareNotifyDeviceID
tptHardwareNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptHardwareNotifySlot.name: tptHardwareNotifySlot
tptHardwareNotifySlot.description: The slot of the hardware whose state has changed. If the hardware element is not a board, this value identifies it as a chassis, fan, power supply, PEM, etc.

tptHardwareNotifyPort.name: tptHardwareNotifyPort
tptHardwareNotifyPort.description: The port or sub-unit number of the hardware whose state has changed. Zero for a board, chassis, fan controller, power supply, or power entry module.

tptHardwareNotifyMeType.name: tptHardwareNotifyMeType
tptHardwareNotifyMeType.description: The type of the managed element (e.g., backplane, controller, power supply, fan, etc.) whose state has changed.

tptHardwareNotifyCfgType.name: tptHardwareNotifyCfgType
tptHardwareNotifyCfgType.description: The configuration/redundancy of the hardware whose state has changed.

tptHardwareNotifyHlState.name: tptHardwareNotifyHlState
tptHardwareNotifyHlState.description: The high-level hardware state (active, initializing, standby, etc.).

tptHardwareNotifyHlStateQual.name: tptHardwareNotifyHlStateQual
tptHardwareNotifyHlStateQual.description: Further qualification/detail on the high-level state.

tptHardwareNotify.name: tptHardwareNotify
tptHardwareNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station of changes in hardware state on the device.
